# Test Preparation for Qwen and Kimi K2.6 Coding Tests

This directory contains preparation for coding tests using Qwen series and Kimi K2.6 models via Kilo Code/KiloClaw.

Plan:
1. Create a simple coding task (e.g., Fibonacci function) in a file task.py.
2. Spawn two subagent sessions:
   - One using Qwen model (e.g., qwen-coder-plus)
   - One using Kimi K2.6 model
3. Each agent will read the task, implement the solution, and write result to output files.
4. Collect outputs for comparison.

Instructions for agents will be provided via session spawning.